 {"id":"frankenjax-g6ap","title":"Conv panics on zero stride parameter","description":"[HIGH] crates/fj-lax/src/tensor_ops.rs accepts strides=0 for Primitive::Conv and then performs division by that stride instead of returning a typed EvalError. In 1D conv, eval_conv_1d parses params[\"strides\"] at lines 2817-2820 and then uses width.div_ceil(stride) for SAME padding at line 2824 or (width - kernel_w) / stride for VALID padding at line 2835. In 2D conv, parse_stride_pair returns zero at lines 2976-2986 and compute_output_and_pad divides by stride at lines 2997 and 3005.\n\nRepro: construct lhs TensorValue::new(DType::F32, Shape { dims: vec![1, 3, 1] }, three F32 literals) and rhs TensorValue::new(DType::F32, Shape { dims: vec![1, 1, 1] }, one F32 literal), set params { \"strides\": \"0\", \"padding\": \"valid\" }, then call eval_primitive(Primitive::Conv, &[lhs, rhs], &params). Current debug/test builds panic on division by zero; release builds can also compute invalid output geometry.\n\nExpected: reject zero or malformed strides before arithmetic with a typed EvalError::Unsupported such as \"conv stride must be positive\". Add regression tests for 1D VALID, 1D SAME, and 2D zero-stride inputs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T07:59:03.422575206Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T08:12:50.439740643Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T08:12:50.437901752Z","close_reason":"Rejected zero and malformed Conv strides before output geometry arithmetic","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}

